title: Bilal Yamin  wins PP-6 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan Muslim League- Nawaz Muhammad Bilal Yamin won the election from Punjab Assembly constituency PP-6 Murree by securing 65,056 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was an independent candidate Zain Ul Abidin who got 33,475 votes.
Votersâ€™ turnout remained at 56.32 per cent.
